race.comment: DE LOUVIERE (19) opened this prep with a couple of nice runs then didn't finish off as hoped over 1900m at Canterbury last time out. Given a bit of time to get over that run and back at the provincials is worth another chance. YABBY PUMP (6) has been just behind the placings at his last couple. Been up for a while now but at this level continues to be competitive. Must go in the numbers. SUNSOURCE (4) was in the market last start over 1900m but pulled up lame a long way behind the leading pack. Went close the run prior in town. Can bounce back. CUESTA (10) is new to this trip but rarely runs a bad race so should give backers a sight.
